1
00:02:23,852 --> 00:02:25,061
Put that down.

2
00:02:28,648 --> 00:02:30,150
That little bitch…

3
00:02:32,152 --> 00:02:34,279
I'm gonna slit her throat and kill her.

4
00:02:34,779 --> 00:02:36,573
Why don't you kill me instead?

5
00:02:39,033 --> 00:02:41,035
I made a move on <i>her</i>.

6
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:46,332
You're lying.

7
00:02:47,333 --> 00:02:48,543
It's the truth.

8
00:02:50,044 --> 00:02:51,963
Chiyoko didn't do anything wrong.

9
00:02:55,341 --> 00:02:56,676
Why are you lying?

10
00:02:58,094 --> 00:03:00,388
Suddenly your loyalty is to her?!

11
00:03:02,223 --> 00:03:04,726
So you're telling these lies
to protect her?!

12
00:03:05,226 --> 00:03:07,312
And I guess sex with her
was really that good?!

13
00:03:07,395 --> 00:03:08,521
I've had enough of your shit!

14
00:03:09,272 --> 00:03:11,274
Where's that bitch? I'll kill her!

15
00:03:13,443 --> 00:03:14,611
Kazuko!

16
00:03:14,694 --> 00:03:15,737
Stop it!

17
00:03:37,592 --> 00:03:38,760
We're done.

18
00:04:59,632 --> 00:05:01,384
Please wait here for a moment.

19
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:55,563
We hope you'll have
a relaxing stay with us, ma'am.

20
00:06:06,032 --> 00:06:10,078
<i>How is your afternoon</i>
<i>shaping up today? Ready for a treat?</i>

21
00:06:10,161 --> 00:06:13,122
<i>I'm Kaoru Jindaiji,</i>
<i>the host of </i>Kaoru's Moment<i>.</i>

22
00:06:13,206 --> 00:06:14,916
<i>Thanks for joining us.</i>

23
00:06:14,999 --> 00:06:17,502
<i>It's a great honor</i>
<i>to present today's guest to you.</i>

24
00:06:17,585 --> 00:06:20,004
<i>Please welcome Chiyoko Shimakura-san!</i>

25
00:06:20,088 --> 00:06:21,714
<i>Hello, come on in.</i>

26
00:06:21,798 --> 00:06:24,759
<i>Thank you for having me.</i>
<i>It's been quite a long time.</i>

27
00:06:24,842 --> 00:06:26,803
<i>Oh, yes, it's been far too long, dear.</i>

28
00:06:26,886 --> 00:06:28,471
<i>Yes, it really has been.</i>

29
00:06:28,554 --> 00:06:32,433
<i>I believe that the last time</i>
<i>we met was… four years ago, is that right?</i>

30
00:06:32,517 --> 00:06:34,560
<i>Oh, really? Has it been that long already?</i>

31
00:06:34,644 --> 00:06:36,270
<i>So let's get to it.</i>

32
00:06:36,354 --> 00:06:39,524
<i>These last four years</i>
<i>have been quite trying for you.</i>

33
00:06:39,607 --> 00:06:40,483
<i>Yes.</i>

34
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:42,819
<i>There's been quite a lot. That's true.</i>

35
00:06:42,902 --> 00:06:45,238
<i>So how did you get through it all?</i>

36
00:06:49,409 --> 00:06:52,537
<i>I suppose… that singing got me through it.</i>

37
00:06:52,620 --> 00:06:54,205
<i>Oh, I see.</i>

38
00:06:54,831 --> 00:06:59,377
<i>Singing got you through it.</i>
<i>What a wonderfully profound thing.</i>

39
00:07:00,586 --> 00:07:02,505
<i>So how are you feeling now?</i>

40
00:07:03,381 --> 00:07:04,757
<i>Hmm…</i>

41
00:07:08,719 --> 00:07:12,765
<i>A little like</i>
<i>I've… just been released from prison.</i>

42
00:07:12,849 --> 00:07:16,018
<i>Oh! Well, that must be a relief.</i>

43
00:07:18,062 --> 00:07:20,648
<i>I hear you've got a new song</i>
<i>coming out soon, right?</i>

44
00:07:20,731 --> 00:07:24,068
<i>Yes. It'll be the first release</i>
<i>from my new label.</i>

45
00:07:49,802 --> 00:07:55,266
<i>Each place I go</i>

46
00:07:56,559 --> 00:08:02,356
<i>Only the lonely go</i>

47
00:08:03,483 --> 00:08:07,904
<i>Some little small…</i>

48
00:08:10,573 --> 00:08:13,284
<i>Café…</i>

49
00:08:15,244 --> 00:08:16,370
Good evening.

50
00:08:17,663 --> 00:08:19,165
Whiskey, please.

51
00:08:19,665 --> 00:08:23,044
Which would you prefer? Bourbon or Scotch?

52
00:08:23,127 --> 00:08:25,838
Either is fine. Neat, please.

53
00:08:26,464 --> 00:08:27,465
Right away.

54
00:08:31,677 --> 00:08:38,518
<i>Recalls a love that used to be</i>

55
00:08:39,018 --> 00:08:45,274
<i>The dreams I dream</i>

56
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:49,153
<i>Only the lonely…</i>

57
00:08:51,405 --> 00:08:53,157
You might not wanna do that.

58
00:08:53,908 --> 00:08:56,452
Getting dumped by a man
isn't worth the hangover.

59
00:08:58,788 --> 00:09:00,248
I'm sorry.

60
00:09:00,331 --> 00:09:02,625
I saw you two at the inn earlier.

61
00:09:04,377 --> 00:09:06,629
I know it's none of my business,

62
00:09:08,130 --> 00:09:09,757
but when you've been hurt,

63
00:09:10,841 --> 00:09:13,219
you should always
put your own needs first.

64
00:09:16,347 --> 00:09:19,809
<i>That soon somewhere</i>

65
00:09:19,892 --> 00:09:21,519
He didn't dump me.

66
00:09:22,645 --> 00:09:25,189
Oh… I see.

67
00:09:26,482 --> 00:09:28,150
It was the other way around.

68
00:09:28,234 --> 00:09:32,655
<i>And you recall</i>

69
00:09:34,156 --> 00:09:36,492
You're quite blunt, aren't you?

70
00:09:36,576 --> 00:09:38,578
I wasn't expecting that
from someone like you.

71
00:09:38,661 --> 00:09:41,372
It's a lot easier
to open up to a stranger.

72
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:45,418
And to complicate things,

73
00:09:45,501 --> 00:09:49,797
the woman the man says
he's divorcing is actually

74
00:09:51,215 --> 00:09:52,883
my very best friend.

75
00:09:54,552 --> 00:09:57,346
So you stole your best friend's husband,
did you?

76
00:09:58,055 --> 00:10:02,393
Knowing that I was hurting her,
just… just tore me apart.

77
00:10:04,812 --> 00:10:07,773
When I saw how happy
they looked at their wedding,

78
00:10:08,482 --> 00:10:10,693
I'd already decided to let him go.

79
00:10:12,737 --> 00:10:14,864
I wonder if the wife

80
00:10:15,364 --> 00:10:17,658
feels like this is a Void Period.

81
00:10:19,118 --> 00:10:20,453
Void Period?

82
00:10:21,078 --> 00:10:23,998
It's a term from Sanmeigaku,
a kind of fortune-telling,

83
00:10:24,081 --> 00:10:27,293
and it refers to a period of time
when the flow of luck is bad.

84
00:10:27,376 --> 00:10:28,544
Wow.

85
00:10:29,086 --> 00:10:31,631
How come you know so much about this?

86
00:10:36,177 --> 00:10:37,803
I suppose

87
00:10:39,096 --> 00:10:40,681
it's because

88
00:10:41,766 --> 00:10:43,559
I'm a fortune teller.

89
00:10:46,979 --> 00:10:48,481
That's wonderful!

90
00:10:48,564 --> 00:10:53,527
Would you mind checking to see
if he and I are compatible?

91
00:10:56,614 --> 00:10:58,449
Do you have a pen I could use?

92
00:10:58,532 --> 00:10:59,450
Sure.

93
00:11:00,534 --> 00:11:05,247
Start by writing down your name and his,
as well as both your birthdates.

94
00:11:05,873 --> 00:11:06,832
All right.

95
00:11:38,614 --> 00:11:40,199
Oh, I see.

96
00:11:41,367 --> 00:11:42,910
Ritsuko, listen.

97
00:11:43,536 --> 00:11:44,370
Okay.

98
00:11:45,663 --> 00:11:47,957
Your compatibility with this man

99
00:11:48,457 --> 00:11:49,959
is very good.

100
00:11:50,042 --> 00:11:51,711
It's almost too good.

101
00:11:51,794 --> 00:11:53,838
Really?

102
00:11:54,338 --> 00:11:55,423
However,

103
00:11:56,006 --> 00:11:58,592
with this kind of compatibility,
there's a downside.

104
00:11:58,676 --> 00:12:01,721
If the two of you are in a lucky phase,
you'll both rise together.

105
00:12:02,221 --> 00:12:03,848
But when your luck is bad,

106
00:12:04,348 --> 00:12:07,601
each of you will drag each other down
and make everything worse.

107
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:10,104
But

108
00:12:11,522 --> 00:12:13,149
the problem starts with you.

109
00:12:14,358 --> 00:12:15,651
At this moment,

110
00:12:16,277 --> 00:12:18,988
you're right in the middle
of a Void Period.

111
00:12:20,531 --> 00:12:25,119
If you bind yourself to anyone right now,
it will end in misfortune.

112
00:12:27,121 --> 00:12:28,622
Mis… misfortune?

113
00:12:30,499 --> 00:12:32,084
Well, there's always

114
00:12:33,794 --> 00:12:37,673
a chance that he might kill himself,
isn't there?

115
00:12:37,757 --> 00:12:42,261
Or it could be his wife as well.

116
00:12:42,344 --> 00:12:44,472
Misato? Oh no.

117
00:12:44,555 --> 00:12:46,599
The kanji for "kill"
used in "killing yourself"

118
00:12:46,682 --> 00:12:48,517
is the same one used in "Void Period."

119
00:12:48,601 --> 00:12:51,645
And there's no guarantee the same "kill"
won't come back around to you.

120
00:12:51,729 --> 00:12:53,314
Which means…

121
00:12:53,397 --> 00:12:57,109
Wait, are you saying
that Misato might kill me?

122
00:12:57,193 --> 00:13:00,946
I use statistics in my fortune-telling.
These are just possible outcomes.

123
00:13:03,991 --> 00:13:06,494
So, what should I do, then?

124
00:13:07,745 --> 00:13:09,497
Only you can choose.

125
00:13:10,998 --> 00:13:11,832
But…

126
00:13:14,627 --> 00:13:16,921
if you don't mind my humble opinion,

127
00:13:18,297 --> 00:13:21,383
before the three of you
tear each other to ruins…

128
00:13:24,512 --> 00:13:26,597
I think you should break it off.

129
00:13:45,533 --> 00:13:49,328
Bartender,
could I please have another whiskey?

130
00:13:50,830 --> 00:13:51,872
Certainly.

131
00:14:13,269 --> 00:14:15,855
- Oh. Are you all right?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

132
00:14:16,438 --> 00:14:17,648
- Careful now.
- Yes.

133
00:14:17,731 --> 00:14:19,608
Whoa.

134
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:21,402
You've had quite a bit.

135
00:14:21,485 --> 00:14:23,237
Yeah, I drank too much.

136
00:14:24,738 --> 00:14:25,990
Thank you again.

137
00:14:26,073 --> 00:14:28,367
I can't believe you paid for my drinks.

138
00:14:28,450 --> 00:14:29,952
Consider it a parting gift.

139
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:34,915
You'll find a better man
and build a happy family.

140
00:14:34,999 --> 00:14:37,126
I'm absolutely sure of that.

141
00:14:38,168 --> 00:14:39,336
I hope so.

142
00:14:40,170 --> 00:14:43,340
Oh, Hosoki-san,
I'm actually headed back that way.

143
00:14:43,424 --> 00:14:46,594
Ah. Well, you take care of yourself.

144
00:14:46,677 --> 00:14:47,511
I will.

145
00:14:48,679 --> 00:14:49,638
Oh, wait.

146
00:14:56,228 --> 00:14:57,062
Here.

147
00:14:57,563 --> 00:14:58,856
I don't need it anymore,

148
00:14:59,356 --> 00:15:00,774
and I'd like to thank you.

149
00:15:01,525 --> 00:15:02,359
Oh.

150
00:15:03,027 --> 00:15:05,446
Isn't that quite a bit more
than a thank-you?

151
00:15:06,530 --> 00:15:10,910
Well… consider it a fee
for your fortune-telling, then.

152
00:15:11,869 --> 00:15:15,998
Your reading really was worth
at least this much.

153
00:15:16,790 --> 00:15:18,876
Ah. Are you sure?

154
00:15:20,753 --> 00:15:25,257
Well, then… I will accept it gratefully.

155
00:15:31,597 --> 00:15:33,265
Thanks. I'll be off.

156
00:15:34,767 --> 00:15:35,768
Take care, now.

157
00:15:36,268 --> 00:15:37,102
I will.

158
00:16:33,158 --> 00:16:37,621
<i>So that was how Kazuko</i>
<i>started off her fortune-telling career?</i>

159
00:16:38,580 --> 00:16:39,498
Yeah.

160
00:16:40,249 --> 00:16:42,126
Something just clicked for her.

161
00:16:42,710 --> 00:16:46,755
I think she realized she had
a natural gift for fortune-telling.

162
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:50,801
More importantly,
she realized it could bring in money.

163
00:16:51,301 --> 00:16:54,888
So, after Shimakura,
she decided to become a fortune teller.

164
00:16:55,889 --> 00:16:57,850
Kazuko's greatest gift

165
00:16:58,976 --> 00:17:02,312
is that once she sets her sights
on something, she always gets it.

166
00:17:04,481 --> 00:17:07,735
<i>First, she apprenticed</i>
<i>with a fortune teller she knew.</i>

167
00:17:07,818 --> 00:17:09,820
<i>She started studying the basics.</i>

168
00:17:09,903 --> 00:17:12,239
To learn the basics
of the Four Pillars of Destiny,

169
00:17:12,322 --> 00:17:13,574
start with these.

170
00:17:14,450 --> 00:17:16,493
Thank you so much for this.

171
00:17:17,536 --> 00:17:21,331
Never try to read someone's fortune
with just superficial knowledge.

172
00:17:22,166 --> 00:17:25,002
Fortune-telling
can alter people's destinies.

173
00:17:25,919 --> 00:17:28,005
If you want to be considered
competent in the field,

174
00:17:28,088 --> 00:17:29,965
you'll need to study
for at least ten years.

175
00:17:30,841 --> 00:17:32,718
I'll do my very best.

176
00:17:33,385 --> 00:17:34,636
<i>In one year,</i>

177
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:37,639
<i>she somehow pulled off</i>
<i>what took ordinary people ten years.</i>

178
00:17:37,723 --> 00:17:40,142
<i>It wasn't perfect,</i>
<i>but she managed to do it.</i>

179
00:17:40,851 --> 00:17:42,895
<i>She must have studied like mad.</i>

180
00:17:43,979 --> 00:17:45,856
<i>Your compatibility is excellent.</i>

181
00:17:45,939 --> 00:17:48,734
Your physical connection, especially.

182
00:17:50,194 --> 00:17:51,862
And if the two of you decide
to get married,

183
00:17:51,945 --> 00:17:53,238
you'll definitely have children.

184
00:17:53,822 --> 00:17:55,365
<i>Under the cover of her business,</i>

185
00:17:55,449 --> 00:17:59,036
<i>she used anyone she could</i>
<i>as a test subject for her readings.</i>

186
00:17:59,119 --> 00:18:02,122
<i>It was the perfect way</i>
<i>to gain hands-on experience.</i>

187
00:18:02,623 --> 00:18:05,709
Hosoki-san,
could you do a reading for us too?

188
00:18:05,793 --> 00:18:06,627
Yes, of course.

189
00:18:07,461 --> 00:18:11,507
<i>She'd been caught in the whirlpool</i>
<i>of nightlife for over 20 years.</i>

190
00:18:11,590 --> 00:18:14,176
<i>She knew about human desire</i>
<i>better than anyone</i>

191
00:18:14,259 --> 00:18:16,678
<i>and applied it to her fortune-telling.</i>

192
00:18:16,762 --> 00:18:20,349
<i>She knew how to write about the things</i>
<i>that grabbed her readers' attention.</i>

193
00:18:22,976 --> 00:18:25,562
<i>She managed to pull some strings</i>
<i>and fast-tracked her manuscript</i>

194
00:18:25,646 --> 00:18:27,272
<i>into a publisher's hands.</i>

195
00:18:27,356 --> 00:18:29,691
<i>But of course, that wasn't the end of it.</i>

196
00:18:31,026 --> 00:18:34,780
<i>She traveled the country on her own dime,</i>
<i>promoting the book herself.</i>

197
00:18:35,447 --> 00:18:39,284
<i>She even roped in celebrity regulars</i>
<i>from the club to advertise the book.</i>

198
00:18:39,785 --> 00:18:42,788
<i>In the blink of an eye,</i>
<i>she'd sold half a million copies.</i>

199
00:18:44,414 --> 00:18:45,582
<i>You gotta hand it to her.</i>

200
00:18:56,635 --> 00:19:01,306
Our country has come out
of a difficult period with our oil crisis,

201
00:19:01,807 --> 00:19:05,310
becoming stronger
and materially wealthier because of it.

202
00:19:05,394 --> 00:19:09,022
However, it is our spiritual richness
that is lacking.

203
00:19:10,399 --> 00:19:12,568
Juvenile crime continues to rise,

204
00:19:12,651 --> 00:19:14,778
and many innocent women and children

205
00:19:14,862 --> 00:19:18,031
continue to fall prey
to brutal crimes committed against them.

206
00:19:18,532 --> 00:19:23,328
Through my style of fortune-telling,
I hope to make this world a better place.

207
00:19:23,912 --> 00:19:26,540
I hope to write
many more books on this subject

208
00:19:26,623 --> 00:19:30,502
so that I can further my reach
to as many people as possible.

209
00:19:31,211 --> 00:19:32,754
With your continued support,

210
00:19:32,838 --> 00:19:34,965
I believe I can make a difference
in this world.

211
00:19:35,048 --> 00:19:38,385
So I wanna say thank you all so much.

212
00:19:49,021 --> 00:19:51,440
<i>It's an incredible feat,</i>
<i>bringing peace of mind to people</i>

213
00:19:51,523 --> 00:19:52,482
<i>through fortune-telling.</i>

214
00:19:52,566 --> 00:19:56,153
You're like Queen Himiko,
who ruled her people through divination.

215
00:19:56,236 --> 00:19:58,614
- You're exaggerating.
- Well, listen, Sensei.

216
00:19:58,697 --> 00:20:02,034
Maybe I could ask you to read my fortune
to see if I'll win next year's election.

217
00:20:02,117 --> 00:20:04,786
Unfortunately,
my schedule is fully booked right now,

218
00:20:04,870 --> 00:20:06,914
but I'm sure we can schedule something.

219
00:20:06,997 --> 00:20:09,249
- I look forward to working with you.
- And with you as well.

220
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:11,501
- Yashiro-sensei!
- Oh, excuse me.

221
00:20:11,585 --> 00:20:13,086
We've been expecting you, sir.

222
00:20:18,008 --> 00:20:19,259
Yashiro-sensei.

223
00:20:19,343 --> 00:20:21,595
- Hey, come here!
- Welcome, Yashiro-sensei.

224
00:20:22,179 --> 00:20:24,681
Who is that man? The guy over there.

225
00:20:27,893 --> 00:20:32,022
The publishing industry is certainly
going through a very difficult period.

226
00:20:32,105 --> 00:20:33,857
- But this kind of--
- Yashiro-sensei.

227
00:20:35,108 --> 00:20:37,861
Very pleased to meet you.
I'm Kazuko Hosoki.

228
00:20:38,904 --> 00:20:41,698
The pleasure is mine, Hosoki-san.
I'm Yashiro--

229
00:20:41,782 --> 00:20:45,202
Yashiro-san. Of course I know who you are.

230
00:20:45,702 --> 00:20:48,664
You're the vice chairman
of the Shigaku Association.

231
00:20:48,747 --> 00:20:50,832
It's an absolute honor to have you here.

232
00:20:50,916 --> 00:20:54,253
Oh? So then
you're familiar with our association?

233
00:20:54,336 --> 00:20:56,713
It's Japan's
most prestigious academic association,

234
00:20:56,797 --> 00:20:59,591
founded by Masataka Yasunaga-sensei,

235
00:20:59,675 --> 00:21:02,261
the longtime adviser
to many prime ministers.

236
00:21:02,761 --> 00:21:05,722
It would be impossible
for anyone here to not have heard of it.

237
00:21:05,806 --> 00:21:07,849
I look forward to getting to know you.

238
00:21:16,817 --> 00:21:18,193
Yashiro-san,

239
00:21:19,486 --> 00:21:25,158
I'd like to broaden my knowledge
and truly master Six-Star Astrology.

240
00:21:26,034 --> 00:21:27,577
If it wouldn't be too much to ask,

241
00:21:27,661 --> 00:21:31,999
would it be possible for you
to introduce me to Yasunaga-sensei?

242
00:21:32,582 --> 00:21:35,252
Yasunaga-sensei, huh?
That man is legendary, you know.

243
00:21:35,335 --> 00:21:38,672
Just getting to be in a room with him
becomes a legendary story.

244
00:21:39,172 --> 00:21:40,841
It's not something that happens easily.

245
00:21:43,427 --> 00:21:44,970
Oh, I see.

246
00:21:46,305 --> 00:21:48,849
Someone as insignificant as I am

247
00:21:49,349 --> 00:21:51,101
should have known better, I guess.

248
00:21:56,440 --> 00:21:58,025
<i>Six months later,</i>

249
00:21:58,525 --> 00:22:01,903
<i>Kazuko became Masataka Yasunaga's wife.</i>

250
00:22:06,325 --> 00:22:10,078
Once she established her fortune-telling,
she set her sights on Yasunaga.

251
00:22:10,162 --> 00:22:15,334
Yes, and once she became his wife,
well, she was basically an icon.

252
00:22:15,417 --> 00:22:18,545
But… how did she manage to do it?

253
00:22:19,171 --> 00:22:20,630
I really don't know.

254
00:22:21,465 --> 00:22:23,967
I was wrapped up
in my own election back then.

255
00:22:26,178 --> 00:22:28,388
You should visit the Yasunaga family.

256
00:22:28,472 --> 00:22:30,182
His daughter might have more information.

257
00:22:30,265 --> 00:22:32,684
<i>Welcome back to this week's episode of</i>

258
00:22:32,768 --> 00:22:34,644
I'll Give It To You Straight-Up!

259
00:22:34,728 --> 00:22:38,899
<i>Please give a warm welcome</i>
<i>to Kazuko Hosoki-sensei!</i>

260
00:22:41,151 --> 00:22:42,861
<i>Yes, yes!</i>

261
00:22:44,905 --> 00:22:48,075
<i>Okay! We have</i>
<i>a wonderful show for you today.</i>

262
00:22:48,158 --> 00:22:49,409
- Shin-san.
- Yeah?

263
00:22:49,910 --> 00:22:51,078
Check, please.

264
00:24:19,207 --> 00:24:24,463
OSAMU MIYAZAWA: CAN WE MEET SOON?
I WANT TO TALK ABOUT KAZUKO HOSOKI.

265
00:24:31,761 --> 00:24:33,889
Are you some kind of idiot or what?!

266
00:24:34,389 --> 00:24:35,849
Aren't you supposed to be a lawyer?!

267
00:24:35,932 --> 00:24:38,894
Can't we sue them for defamation and
get damages? There's gotta be something!

268
00:24:38,977 --> 00:24:41,855
<i>Unfortunately, we can only</i>
<i>take action after the article--</i>

269
00:24:41,938 --> 00:24:43,773
After it's out, it'll be too late!

270
00:24:44,399 --> 00:24:47,402
What the hell am I paying you
such a hefty retainer for?!

271
00:24:48,028 --> 00:24:51,072
I don't care how, but you'd better stop
that article from coming out.

272
00:24:51,156 --> 00:24:52,157
Do you hear me?

273
00:25:23,271 --> 00:25:25,315
She's certainly got some nerve.

274
00:25:50,215 --> 00:25:52,592
<i>My father, Masataka Yasunaga,</i>

275
00:25:52,676 --> 00:25:56,471
<i>spent the latter half of his life here</i>
<i>in this house until he passed away.</i>

276
00:25:57,681 --> 00:26:00,600
<i>We decided to turn it</i>
<i>into a memorial museum.</i>

277
00:26:03,311 --> 00:26:05,689
When you first got in touch with me,

278
00:26:06,606 --> 00:26:09,401
I have to admit I was prepared to decline.

279
00:26:11,361 --> 00:26:13,113
I'm sorry for imposing.

280
00:26:13,196 --> 00:26:14,030
But…

281
00:26:14,948 --> 00:26:17,534
Uozumi-san, after I read your novel…

282
00:26:17,617 --> 00:26:18,535
Yes?

283
00:26:19,286 --> 00:26:20,745
…then I changed my mind.

284
00:26:23,039 --> 00:26:24,541
I could feel the love that you poured

285
00:26:24,624 --> 00:26:27,377
into each
and every one of your characters.

286
00:26:28,628 --> 00:26:29,963
And I could tell

287
00:26:30,046 --> 00:26:32,966
that you're a very earnest
and sincere writer.

288
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:35,385
Thank you very much.

289
00:26:35,468 --> 00:26:36,761
I feel that I could trust you…

290
00:26:39,180 --> 00:26:42,851
and that it would be all right
to speak with you about my father.

291
00:26:47,063 --> 00:26:50,984
I can tell you…
everything I saw and heard at the time.

292
00:26:51,568 --> 00:26:53,653
I'm going to be
completely honest with you.

293
00:26:54,946 --> 00:26:57,240
How you choose to write it into the book

294
00:26:57,949 --> 00:26:59,784
will be entirely up to you.

295
00:27:05,332 --> 00:27:08,084
Let's start with your father.
What was he like?

296
00:27:12,422 --> 00:27:14,174
In his later years,

297
00:27:14,674 --> 00:27:17,552
he chose to only wear summer kimonos.

298
00:27:18,637 --> 00:27:20,347
He liked how light they were

299
00:27:20,847 --> 00:27:22,807
and how easy it was to move in them.

300
00:27:28,438 --> 00:27:30,815
He treated everyone

301
00:27:31,441 --> 00:27:34,152
with the same light touch as his kimono.

302
00:27:35,612 --> 00:27:38,490
And he never forced
his opinions on anyone.

303
00:27:38,573 --> 00:27:40,825
Nor must you wait too long.

304
00:27:40,909 --> 00:27:43,703
<i>Anyone and everyone</i>
<i>was welcome to hear him speak.</i>

305
00:27:43,787 --> 00:27:45,288
<i>He never turned anyone away,</i>

306
00:27:45,372 --> 00:27:47,791
<i>and he never chased after</i>
<i>the ones who left.</i>

307
00:27:48,708 --> 00:27:51,628
<i>His brilliance and his open-hearted,</i>
<i>free-spirited nature</i>

308
00:27:51,711 --> 00:27:53,922
<i>captivated and inspired everyone,</i>

309
00:27:54,005 --> 00:27:56,716
<i>from multiple successive prime ministers</i>

310
00:27:56,800 --> 00:27:59,219
<i>to the heads of major corporations.</i>

311
00:28:01,513 --> 00:28:02,931
<i>I suspect that</i>

312
00:28:03,473 --> 00:28:06,226
<i>it was the sheer breadth of his generosity</i>

313
00:28:06,726 --> 00:28:10,438
<i>that made it possible for Hosoki-san</i>
<i>to worm her way into his life.</i>

314
00:28:10,522 --> 00:28:14,693
…governed his life, it begs the question
of whether he was in a position to use it.

315
00:28:21,241 --> 00:28:22,659
Yasunaga-sensei.

316
00:28:23,243 --> 00:28:25,829
There's someone
I'd like to introduce you to.

317
00:28:27,664 --> 00:28:30,291
This is Kazuko Hosoki-san.

318
00:28:30,375 --> 00:28:32,168
Just Kazuko if you wish.

319
00:28:32,252 --> 00:28:34,462
It's an honor and a pleasure to meet you.

320
00:28:36,798 --> 00:28:39,467
Hosoki-san
is a very successful businesswoman

321
00:28:39,551 --> 00:28:42,637
who has recently published
a book on fortune-telling.

322
00:28:42,721 --> 00:28:45,056
- I was hoping you might grant her an--
- Sensei.

323
00:28:46,015 --> 00:28:48,226
I couldn't help but notice
the way you're drinking.

324
00:28:48,309 --> 00:28:50,729
It's truly elegant and refined.

325
00:28:50,812 --> 00:28:52,647
I'm captivated watching you.

326
00:28:55,442 --> 00:28:56,401
Allow me.

327
00:28:59,154 --> 00:28:59,988
Father.

328
00:29:01,156 --> 00:29:02,699
That's quite enough.

329
00:29:03,783 --> 00:29:06,953
Even wise men need a bit
of simulation now and then.

330
00:29:07,036 --> 00:29:10,540
Would you really begrudge me
that simple pleasure in this little glass?

331
00:29:10,623 --> 00:29:11,875
Well, in that case,

332
00:29:12,876 --> 00:29:14,836
why not drink using this?

333
00:29:14,919 --> 00:29:17,922
Uh, Kazuko, please. You've gone too far.

334
00:29:19,716 --> 00:29:21,050
Brilliant idea.

335
00:29:21,134 --> 00:29:22,552
Go ahead and pour it.

336
00:29:28,349 --> 00:29:30,643
Your movements are quite assured.

337
00:29:31,352 --> 00:29:33,730
Well, actually, for the last 20 years,

338
00:29:33,813 --> 00:29:36,983
I've mostly been involved
in the nightlife business.

339
00:29:37,484 --> 00:29:40,028
Then why did you write a book
on divination?

340
00:29:40,528 --> 00:29:44,741
It was your book, <i>I Ching and Life,</i>
that inspired me to write mine.

341
00:29:46,326 --> 00:29:48,703
I was deeply affected by what you wrote.

342
00:29:49,204 --> 00:29:53,458
So then I devoted myself
to mastering the Four Pillars of Destiny,

343
00:29:53,541 --> 00:29:55,460
which was your recommendation.

344
00:30:02,091 --> 00:30:03,760
Don't lie to me.

345
00:30:03,843 --> 00:30:07,555
I would never lie.
I studied it obsessively, and I--

346
00:30:07,639 --> 00:30:09,891
That book was published four years ago.

347
00:30:10,892 --> 00:30:14,103
Even the greatest prodigy needs
at least ten years

348
00:30:14,187 --> 00:30:16,564
to master destiny analysis.

349
00:30:16,648 --> 00:30:19,150
You worked in the nightlife industry.

350
00:30:19,651 --> 00:30:21,569
Were you truly able
to devote yourself to it

351
00:30:21,653 --> 00:30:24,239
more than a prodigy
with ten years could have?

352
00:30:24,322 --> 00:30:27,867
If not, then I'm afraid your book
is nothing but a distortion.

353
00:30:32,580 --> 00:30:33,998
I'm sorry.

354
00:30:35,792 --> 00:30:38,044
I made a terrible and foolish mistake

355
00:30:38,127 --> 00:30:41,005
thinking I could ever converse
with you, Sensei.

356
00:30:44,300 --> 00:30:45,969
Please, Kazuko!

357
00:30:46,052 --> 00:30:49,556
All I wanted
was to learn from you, Sensei.

358
00:30:49,639 --> 00:30:51,307
Stop. This is shameful.

359
00:30:51,391 --> 00:30:53,309
But I… I just…

360
00:30:54,602 --> 00:30:56,980
It's… it's all right. I understand.

361
00:30:57,480 --> 00:31:02,193
Next time, just come to my house.
I'll help you with the basics.

362
00:31:08,324 --> 00:31:11,202
Um, would you mind contacting me here?

363
00:31:12,871 --> 00:31:14,706
Thank you very much.

364
00:31:16,416 --> 00:31:19,294
I guess that having a woman cry over me

365
00:31:19,377 --> 00:31:21,880
means that I still have my charms.

366
00:31:28,052 --> 00:31:31,180
Even wise men need
a bit of simulation now and then.

367
00:31:31,264 --> 00:31:35,101
Would you really begrudge me
that simple pleasure in this little glass?

368
00:31:39,898 --> 00:31:42,358
Very well,
but this is your last drink for today.

369
00:31:47,780 --> 00:31:51,743
<i>My father had begun to show</i>
<i>symptoms of dementia around that time.</i>

370
00:31:54,162 --> 00:31:56,998
<i>I believe that Kazuko sensed it in him</i>

371
00:31:58,583 --> 00:32:00,960
<i>the very first day that they met.</i>

372
00:32:03,713 --> 00:32:05,673
<i>About a month later,</i>

373
00:32:05,757 --> 00:32:10,303
<i>Kazuko came here to the house to speak</i>
<i>to my father and get his mentorship.</i>

374
00:32:22,941 --> 00:32:23,816
Please come in.

375
00:32:23,900 --> 00:32:25,360
Hello, Sensei.

376
00:32:25,443 --> 00:32:28,571
Thank you so very much
for having me in your home.

377
00:32:29,072 --> 00:32:29,989
For you.

378
00:32:30,490 --> 00:32:34,661
This is just a small token of gratitude.
It's a special-grade sake from Niigata.

379
00:32:37,288 --> 00:32:39,415
Thank you for going to the trouble.

380
00:32:42,710 --> 00:32:43,962
One more thing, Father.

381
00:32:48,716 --> 00:32:52,345
You have a medical appointment later,
so please don't smoke today.

382
00:32:56,557 --> 00:32:58,893
I'll come back and let you know
when it's time to finish.

383
00:33:09,487 --> 00:33:11,114
In other words,

384
00:33:11,197 --> 00:33:14,158
the foundation of the <i>I Ching</i>
lies in understanding

385
00:33:14,242 --> 00:33:18,830
how the world changes according
to the interactions of yin and yang.

386
00:33:18,913 --> 00:33:23,292
We must always consider how those changes
be brought into balance.

387
00:33:23,376 --> 00:33:26,713
The patterns of those changes
are represented this way.

388
00:33:26,796 --> 00:33:32,719
As the flow of time,
in the form of the 64 hexagrams.

389
00:33:34,262 --> 00:33:35,221
Hmm.

390
00:33:35,304 --> 00:33:38,141
Hmm. This is very difficult.

391
00:33:38,224 --> 00:33:40,143
At least, it is for me.

392
00:33:41,060 --> 00:33:44,772
I'm worried now that it's too presumptuous
for someone as lowly as me

393
00:33:44,856 --> 00:33:46,733
to even try to learn <i>I Ching.</i>

394
00:33:47,483 --> 00:33:48,609
Hmm.

395
00:33:48,693 --> 00:33:52,905
Vimalakirti, who expounded
the teachings of the Buddha

396
00:33:52,989 --> 00:33:55,158
in the Vimalakirti Sutra,

397
00:33:55,241 --> 00:33:58,953
was a notorious gambler and drunkard.

398
00:33:59,704 --> 00:34:03,583
One's social status
has nothing to do with learning.

399
00:34:04,250 --> 00:34:07,837
Well, I happen to know
quite a lot about drinking and gambling.

400
00:34:08,421 --> 00:34:09,547
Mm.

401
00:34:13,217 --> 00:34:16,429
Ah, would you mind letting some air in?

402
00:34:17,180 --> 00:34:18,097
Yes, sir.

403
00:34:25,188 --> 00:34:26,939
Mastering learning

404
00:34:27,857 --> 00:34:31,778
isn't something that can be achieved
by sitting at a desk.

405
00:34:32,278 --> 00:34:36,991
True learning occurs only
by drawing it out of our daily activities

406
00:34:37,075 --> 00:34:40,703
and harnessing it
in order to reveal what lies beneath.

407
00:34:42,455 --> 00:34:43,956
Harnessing learning?

408
00:34:44,665 --> 00:34:47,168
Yes, that is the core of my philosophy.

409
00:34:47,251 --> 00:34:48,795
The Harnessing of Learning.

410
00:34:54,342 --> 00:34:55,676
As a child,

411
00:34:57,470 --> 00:35:00,139
my family lost everything in the war.

412
00:35:02,225 --> 00:35:04,852
Our house burned down in the air raids,

413
00:35:05,353 --> 00:35:08,022
and my father and brother
were killed in battle.

414
00:35:12,401 --> 00:35:13,903
During the evacuation,

415
00:35:13,986 --> 00:35:17,406
I heard the emperor's speech,
which you had helped to revise.

416
00:35:19,158 --> 00:35:20,118
Mm.

417
00:35:20,201 --> 00:35:22,203
Once I returned to Tokyo,

418
00:35:22,954 --> 00:35:25,790
I helped my mother build up her business.

419
00:35:26,707 --> 00:35:30,253
Except… that wasn't enough
to make a living.

420
00:35:30,878 --> 00:35:35,049
So I dropped out of school
and started working at night.

421
00:35:37,426 --> 00:35:39,303
I was such a naive young girl.

422
00:35:42,473 --> 00:35:44,392
<i>I was almost sold by one man,</i>

423
00:35:45,184 --> 00:35:47,562
then I was bullied
in the family I married into.

424
00:35:50,189 --> 00:35:51,566
I was even swindled…

425
00:35:53,609 --> 00:35:55,653
into hundreds of millions' worth of debt.

426
00:35:57,864 --> 00:35:59,699
I went to the depths of hell.

427
00:36:02,785 --> 00:36:05,037
And that wasn't even all of it.

428
00:36:05,872 --> 00:36:08,749
<i>I was treated like a slave</i>
<i>by a yakuza member.</i>

429
00:36:09,709 --> 00:36:12,170
<i>And even my kindness</i>
<i>in saving someone else's life</i>

430
00:36:12,253 --> 00:36:13,337
<i>was repaid with betrayal.</i>

431
00:36:17,508 --> 00:36:19,468
I thought about ending my life

432
00:36:21,053 --> 00:36:23,097
more times than I care to admit it.

433
00:36:27,435 --> 00:36:29,312
I'm far from perfect.

434
00:36:31,105 --> 00:36:32,607
I have failed,

435
00:36:33,566 --> 00:36:35,818
and I have injured many people,

436
00:36:36,611 --> 00:36:39,071
but I've learned from those experiences.

437
00:36:39,572 --> 00:36:43,034
I've fallen and gotten up
and even failed again,

438
00:36:43,117 --> 00:36:46,245
enduring the worst hardships
just to stay alive.

439
00:36:46,954 --> 00:36:49,790
Only then could I finally learn enough

440
00:36:49,874 --> 00:36:52,835
about the ways of the world
to be able to sit here with you.

441
00:36:54,170 --> 00:36:55,004
All that…

442
00:36:57,048 --> 00:36:58,633
is part of my learning.

443
00:37:03,054 --> 00:37:04,722
Wonderful.

444
00:37:05,806 --> 00:37:06,641
What?

445
00:37:07,225 --> 00:37:08,601
What you've said

446
00:37:09,268 --> 00:37:13,564
is exactly what the Harnessing of Learning
actually is.

447
00:37:16,359 --> 00:37:18,110
I'm truly humbled.

448
00:37:19,111 --> 00:37:21,572
Your praise is far more than I deserve.

449
00:37:25,534 --> 00:37:26,577
It's been ages

450
00:37:26,661 --> 00:37:31,123
since I've heard someone speak words
that were so alive,

451
00:37:31,207 --> 00:37:32,708
with real blood in them.

452
00:37:36,504 --> 00:37:37,755
These days,

453
00:37:37,838 --> 00:37:43,636
all I hear is
just sycophantic flattery and platitudes.

454
00:37:44,929 --> 00:37:48,391
Those who aspire to my teachings
are rather disappointing.

455
00:37:54,480 --> 00:37:55,648
Excuse me.

456
00:37:56,774 --> 00:37:58,276
Father, it's almost time.

457
00:38:00,569 --> 00:38:04,115
Your appointment is very soon,
so we should get ready.

458
00:38:23,050 --> 00:38:24,218
Sensei.

459
00:38:25,219 --> 00:38:26,512
Here you are.

460
00:38:26,595 --> 00:38:28,097
This is my club.

461
00:38:31,100 --> 00:38:34,228
If you happen to be in the neighborhood,
please stop by.

462
00:38:37,732 --> 00:38:39,108
It's very important

463
00:38:39,608 --> 00:38:41,527
to unwind once in a while.

464
00:38:45,990 --> 00:38:48,159
<i>Sometime after that meeting,</i>

465
00:38:48,242 --> 00:38:52,079
<i>my father went out one day</i>
<i>and didn't come home.</i>

466
00:38:52,163 --> 00:38:53,456
- Thank you.
- Of course.

467
00:38:53,539 --> 00:38:56,250
<i>Even though he was showing</i>
<i>symptoms of dementia,</i>

468
00:38:56,751 --> 00:38:59,211
<i>he had never done</i>
<i>anything like this before.</i>

469
00:38:59,295 --> 00:39:02,173
If you find anything out,
please let me know.

470
00:39:04,050 --> 00:39:04,967
Thank you.

471
00:39:06,510 --> 00:39:07,762
Yes, good night.

472
00:39:18,522 --> 00:39:21,233
There you go, Sensei. You're home now.

473
00:39:21,734 --> 00:39:23,027
Father!

474
00:39:23,110 --> 00:39:24,445
Oh, good evening.

475
00:39:24,528 --> 00:39:25,905
Thank goodness you're here.

476
00:39:25,988 --> 00:39:27,907
Father, what happened to you?

477
00:39:27,990 --> 00:39:30,409
I was worried sick. Father?

478
00:39:31,243 --> 00:39:35,414
Uh, do you mind telling me what happened?
How could he have gotten this drunk?

479
00:39:35,498 --> 00:39:37,375
I was keeping him company,

480
00:39:37,458 --> 00:39:39,794
but then I had to step away
for a quick errand.

481
00:39:39,877 --> 00:39:42,171
It seems that he drank quite a bit
while I was gone.

482
00:39:44,382 --> 00:39:47,802
Hosoki-san, he didn't mention anything
to me about going to your club.

483
00:39:49,136 --> 00:39:52,473
I'm afraid it was my fault.
I shouldn't have left him alone.

484
00:39:52,973 --> 00:39:57,645
No, I… I should apologize.
Thank you for bringing him back.

485
00:39:59,814 --> 00:40:02,691
Seems like he smoked quite a bit too.

486
00:40:03,984 --> 00:40:06,779
Next time, I'll make sure
to keep a closer eye on him.

487
00:40:06,862 --> 00:40:10,157
Please tell him that he's welcome
to come by the club anytime.

488
00:40:14,578 --> 00:40:15,996
<i>From that day on,</i>

489
00:40:16,747 --> 00:40:20,751
<i>my father began visiting her club</i>
<i>more and more often.</i>

490
00:40:21,252 --> 00:40:23,337
- Can I have an orange juice, please?
- Sure.

491
00:40:24,380 --> 00:40:25,756
<i>I was worried,</i>

492
00:40:25,840 --> 00:40:29,301
<i>so I had one of my father's</i>
<i>live-in students follow him.</i>

493
00:40:30,970 --> 00:40:34,306
<i>He told me that Kazuko</i>
<i>stayed glued to my father's side,</i>

494
00:40:34,390 --> 00:40:37,518
<i>talking to him incessantly</i>
<i>without letting him rest,</i>

495
00:40:37,601 --> 00:40:40,020
<i>and encouraging him to drink for hours.</i>

496
00:40:47,695 --> 00:40:49,738
Are you okay, Sensei?

497
00:40:49,822 --> 00:40:52,158
<i>That night,</i>
<i>she took my father back to her place</i>

498
00:40:52,241 --> 00:40:53,534
<i>instead of ours.</i>

499
00:40:53,617 --> 00:40:55,494
You've had quite a lot to drink.

500
00:40:56,203 --> 00:40:57,246
Oh.

501
00:41:02,710 --> 00:41:04,545
After my mother passed away,

502
00:41:05,296 --> 00:41:08,382
I was the one who took care of everything
for my father,

503
00:41:08,466 --> 00:41:10,259
and I did it happily.

504
00:41:13,137 --> 00:41:15,681
Being the one
who was that close to my father,

505
00:41:16,390 --> 00:41:18,309
a man admired by everyone…

506
00:41:20,436 --> 00:41:24,356
well, I… I took great pride in it.

507
00:41:26,984 --> 00:41:30,613
And Kazuko took that pride away from you?

508
00:41:32,198 --> 00:41:35,367
I couldn't… I couldn't stand it.

509
00:41:36,535 --> 00:41:39,079
I decided to confront my father.

510
00:42:10,069 --> 00:42:12,863
What's with that look on your face?

511
00:42:12,947 --> 00:42:13,989
The scrolls.

512
00:42:14,573 --> 00:42:16,492
What are you planning to do with them?

513
00:42:17,159 --> 00:42:21,413
Kazuko asked me
to teach her about calligraphy

514
00:42:21,497 --> 00:42:22,998
and how to appreciate it.

515
00:42:24,959 --> 00:42:28,295
You said that once before
but never brought them back.

516
00:42:29,296 --> 00:42:30,130
Huh?

517
00:42:30,798 --> 00:42:33,092
I don't remember that.

518
00:42:34,510 --> 00:42:37,638
Father, you didn't give them
to Hosoki-san, did you?

519
00:42:40,891 --> 00:42:41,976
Please, Father.

520
00:42:42,560 --> 00:42:45,271
Promise me
that you won't go see her anymore.

521
00:42:46,021 --> 00:42:47,231
Towako,

522
00:42:48,148 --> 00:42:51,443
whose benefit do you think
you're saying that for, exactly?

523
00:42:51,527 --> 00:42:53,571
Father, it's for your benefit first.

524
00:42:54,405 --> 00:42:55,781
Not just for you though.

525
00:42:56,490 --> 00:42:58,576
It's for the Yasunaga family name.

526
00:43:00,160 --> 00:43:01,579
And it's also for poor Mother.

527
00:43:01,662 --> 00:43:02,746
Enough.

528
00:43:03,831 --> 00:43:06,083
It's simply all for your benefit.

529
00:43:08,419 --> 00:43:13,132
Stop making me
the anchor for everything in your life.

530
00:43:14,174 --> 00:43:19,013
It's time for you
to live your life just as you please.

531
00:43:25,394 --> 00:43:27,313
And I shall do the same for myself.

532
00:43:45,539 --> 00:43:46,999
You've almost got it.

533
00:43:48,167 --> 00:43:49,293
That's perfect.

534
00:43:49,376 --> 00:43:51,295
So good. Wonderful job.

535
00:43:51,378 --> 00:43:53,005
This is for you.

536
00:43:53,672 --> 00:43:54,673
Oh.

537
00:43:58,052 --> 00:43:58,886
Oh, yes.

538
00:43:58,969 --> 00:44:01,013
Let's put your thumbprint on this
while we're at it.

539
00:44:01,096 --> 00:44:02,097
Oh, sure.

540
00:44:04,642 --> 00:44:05,893
Here we go.

541
00:44:07,227 --> 00:44:09,104
Thank you.

542
00:44:09,188 --> 00:44:10,481
Oh, Sensei.

543
00:44:10,564 --> 00:44:13,442
I was wondering if you would write
a recommendation for my next book?

544
00:44:13,525 --> 00:44:14,693
Oh, sure.

545
00:44:14,777 --> 00:44:17,613
Also, could I please have
the hanging scroll you brought today?

546
00:44:17,696 --> 00:44:19,156
Oh, yes.

547
00:44:19,239 --> 00:44:20,491
Here's your smoke.

548
00:44:20,991 --> 00:44:22,951
Mm.

549
00:44:23,744 --> 00:44:24,578
There.

550
00:44:34,880 --> 00:44:36,215
All right, all right.

551
00:44:45,641 --> 00:44:46,558
Yes?

552
00:44:48,102 --> 00:44:50,104
Oh, Towako-san.

553
00:44:53,732 --> 00:44:55,025
Kazuko!

554
00:44:55,567 --> 00:44:56,860
Kazuko!

555
00:44:57,361 --> 00:44:59,446
- We're out of sake!
- Excuse me.

556
00:44:59,530 --> 00:45:01,031
There's none left!

557
00:45:08,539 --> 00:45:09,915
Oh, Father, no.

558
00:45:11,667 --> 00:45:12,876
Shizuko.

559
00:45:13,502 --> 00:45:15,254
Shizuko, you…

560
00:45:15,963 --> 00:45:18,590
Now, Father,
you've got to get a hold of yourself.

561
00:45:18,674 --> 00:45:20,300
It's me, Towako!

562
00:45:21,385 --> 00:45:23,470
Mother never would have approved of this!

563
00:45:23,554 --> 00:45:24,847
Huh?

564
00:45:24,930 --> 00:45:26,098
Come on.

565
00:45:26,682 --> 00:45:29,101
- We're leaving right now.
- Towako-san.

566
00:45:31,061 --> 00:45:32,146
Listen.

567
00:45:32,646 --> 00:45:35,983
Your father is here of his own free will.
You know that, don't you?

568
00:45:36,567 --> 00:45:38,610
This isn't something
a daughter should interfere with.

569
00:45:41,697 --> 00:45:43,365
His own free will?

570
00:45:45,033 --> 00:45:48,704
You have manipulated him into coming here.

571
00:45:48,787 --> 00:45:50,164
You're wrong about that.

572
00:45:51,165 --> 00:45:53,500
He's my sensei. I'm his disciple.

573
00:45:54,001 --> 00:45:58,005
It's only natural for a disciple
to do what the master wants.

574
00:45:58,088 --> 00:45:59,965
After getting him wasted like this?

575
00:46:00,048 --> 00:46:01,717
You think you're a disciple?

576
00:46:02,259 --> 00:46:03,927
You're nothing but a sham.

577
00:46:04,887 --> 00:46:08,182
A phony, and you're shameless!

578
00:46:13,187 --> 00:46:14,563
Look.

579
00:46:16,523 --> 00:46:18,525
Just because you're his daughter

580
00:46:19,526 --> 00:46:22,654
doesn't mean
that makes you anything special.

581
00:46:27,534 --> 00:46:28,911
Shizuko!

582
00:46:37,294 --> 00:46:38,879
What bliss!

583
00:46:40,005 --> 00:46:42,925
It seems that I have taken back

584
00:46:43,801 --> 00:46:46,178
the freedom of my soul!

585
00:46:50,098 --> 00:46:51,809
Father, what are you doing?

586
00:47:03,403 --> 00:47:05,739
Father! Are you all right?

587
00:47:05,823 --> 00:47:08,033
Father, wake up! Please, Father!

588
00:47:09,243 --> 00:47:12,621
Oh, please, stay with me!

589
00:47:12,704 --> 00:47:15,249
Please, Father! Please!

590
00:47:15,332 --> 00:47:17,376
Father! Father, wake up!

591
00:47:22,756 --> 00:47:24,383
<i>He survived the fall,</i>

592
00:47:24,466 --> 00:47:27,678
<i>but his condition</i>
<i>was still quite critical after that.</i>

593
00:47:27,761 --> 00:47:30,347
<i>And yet…</i>

594
00:47:32,474 --> 00:47:34,268
There's a problem! That woman…

595
00:47:34,351 --> 00:47:35,227
What?

596
00:48:03,046 --> 00:48:04,715
This way, please. Thank you.

597
00:48:32,618 --> 00:48:33,702
Get out of here.

598
00:48:34,202 --> 00:48:36,580
Outsiders like you are not welcome.

599
00:48:36,663 --> 00:48:38,081
An outsider? Me?

600
00:48:41,585 --> 00:48:44,630
WRITTEN OATH
I PROMISE TO MARRY KAZUKO HOSOKI

601
00:48:44,713 --> 00:48:46,131
MASATAKA YASUNAGA
KAZUKO HOSOKI

602
00:48:47,716 --> 00:48:48,550
Is that…?

603
00:48:54,139 --> 00:48:55,557
YASUNAGA
HOSOKI

604
00:48:55,641 --> 00:48:57,225
MARRIAGE REGISTRATION

605
00:49:00,854 --> 00:49:03,065
As his wife, I have a right to see him.

606
00:49:03,148 --> 00:49:04,900
Excuse me, please.

607
00:49:17,245 --> 00:49:19,039
- Sensei!
- Close the door!

608
00:49:23,961 --> 00:49:25,629
Open it!

609
00:49:26,880 --> 00:49:28,090
Open it now!

610
00:49:29,257 --> 00:49:30,968
I want to see him!

611
00:49:32,302 --> 00:49:34,429
Let me see my husband!

612
00:49:34,513 --> 00:49:36,890
I'm his wife! You can't do this to me!

613
00:49:36,974 --> 00:49:38,350
Let me see my husband!

614
00:49:39,059 --> 00:49:40,936
Please! I want to see him!

615
00:49:42,229 --> 00:49:44,606
Open the door right now!

616
00:49:44,690 --> 00:49:45,899
<i>At that moment,</i>

617
00:49:46,942 --> 00:49:48,735
I remember thinking

618
00:49:50,320 --> 00:49:54,074
that I would never, ever…
forgive that woman.

619
00:49:54,157 --> 00:49:55,909
Not even after I died.

620
00:50:02,499 --> 00:50:03,959
Open it!

621
00:50:04,835 --> 00:50:06,503
Open it!

622
00:50:07,337 --> 00:50:09,756
I wanna see my husband!

623
00:50:09,840 --> 00:50:11,216
Open!

624
00:50:11,717 --> 00:50:13,927
I wanna see my husband!

625
00:50:16,138 --> 00:50:18,974
I wanna see him, please!

626
00:50:31,778 --> 00:50:33,613
Hey there. Sorry I'm late.

627
00:50:40,871 --> 00:50:42,539
Hey, it's been a while, huh?

628
00:50:43,582 --> 00:50:47,502
I think this might be
the first time since the divorce.

629
00:50:48,003 --> 00:50:49,463
What do you want, Osamu?

630
00:50:51,339 --> 00:50:53,133
No small talk, I guess.

631
00:50:54,426 --> 00:50:56,011
It's about Kazuko, right?

632
00:50:58,597 --> 00:51:01,349
How's the, uh, book coming along?

633
00:51:01,433 --> 00:51:03,852
There's not much yet.
I just started writing it.

634
00:51:04,352 --> 00:51:05,479
Okay.

635
00:51:06,438 --> 00:51:08,815
Could you please get to the point?

636
00:51:14,446 --> 00:51:17,908
Look, Kazuko Hosoki
still has ties to the yakuza,

637
00:51:17,991 --> 00:51:21,036
and she's basically running
a spiritual scam, right?

638
00:51:22,079 --> 00:51:23,830
There's plenty of dirt in her past.

639
00:51:23,914 --> 00:51:26,166
It all comes pouring out
if you dig a little.

640
00:51:26,917 --> 00:51:28,126
Who told you?

641
00:51:28,210 --> 00:51:31,129
Our weekly magazine
is prepping a new campaign

642
00:51:31,213 --> 00:51:33,173
that'll expose Hosoki's dark side.

643
00:51:34,966 --> 00:51:39,888
Hosoki found out about the article
and is apparently desperate to kill it.

644
00:51:39,971 --> 00:51:43,183
She's been threatening us
through her lawyer.

645
00:51:43,975 --> 00:51:46,853
Obviously, we refused to back down.

646
00:51:51,399 --> 00:51:52,234
Look, Minori,

647
00:51:53,276 --> 00:51:55,862
did you get that book offer
about two months ago?

648
00:51:56,655 --> 00:51:57,864
Yeah, I did.

649
00:51:57,948 --> 00:52:01,243
That's exactly when the exposé
started gaining traction.

650
00:52:05,413 --> 00:52:07,457
They're using you as a decoy, Minori.

651
00:52:08,041 --> 00:52:09,876
I'll bet they want you to write a story

652
00:52:09,960 --> 00:52:12,003
that makes Hosoki look good
to counter the article.

653
00:52:15,298 --> 00:52:17,968
I know how much
you wanna publish another novel.

654
00:52:18,051 --> 00:52:20,554
Maybe you feel like
you've got something to prove.

655
00:52:20,637 --> 00:52:22,848
But this time,
you really should walk away.

656
00:52:23,348 --> 00:52:26,810
Otherwise, you'll just end up
being a gimmick, and then it'll be over.

657
00:52:51,459 --> 00:52:53,461
Ah, hello, ma'am. It's Tetchan.

658
00:52:55,839 --> 00:52:58,466
I see. She's quite the handful.

659
00:53:00,093 --> 00:53:03,471
No, that's all right.
I have a plan of my own.

660
00:53:04,431 --> 00:53:05,724
Thank you, Tetchan.

661
00:53:06,266 --> 00:53:10,312
Things are a bit sensitive right now,
so I'll send your payment in the mail.

662
00:53:12,647 --> 00:53:13,607
Goodbye.
